---
import { LinkButton } from "@astrojs/starlight/components";
import { PackageManagers } from "starlight-package-managers";
---

<div class="try-it-out">
	<h2>
		Try out <a href="https://github.com/JoshuaKGoldberg/create-typescript-app"
			>create-typescript-app</a
		>, built with Bingo:
	</h2>

	<PackageManagers type="dlx" pkg="create-typescript-app" />

	<p>
		Frustrated setting up an endless list of tooling configuration files?
		<br />
		Tired of dependencies breaking changes in your repositories?
		<br />
		<br />
		Let a package built on Bingo manage it all for you.
		<br />
		<br />
		<LinkButton href="/about">Get started</LinkButton>
	</p>
</div>

<style>
	.try-it-out {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 2rem;
		margin: auto;
		max-width: 49rem;
		padding-top: 4rem;
	}

	h2,
	p {
		text-align: center;
	}

	p {
		font-size: var(--sl-text-xl);
	}
</style>
